---
import ReportLayout from "../../../layouts/ReportLayout.astro";
import Section from "../../../components/Section.astro";
import DiagramFigure from "../../../components/diagrams/DiagramFigure.astro";
import DesktopMainCompositionFlow from "../../../components/diagrams/DesktopMainCompositionFlow.astro";
import { chapterHref, chapterNavItems } from "../../../lib/chapters";
import { chrome, localePath } from "../../../lib/i18n";

const locale = "en" as const;
const nav = chapterNavItems(locale);
const t = chrome(locale);
const selfHref = localePath(locale, "guides/desktop-host");
const ch01 = chapterHref("01-log-is-the-runtime", locale);
const ch02 = chapterHref("02-evidence-before-compression", locale);
---

<ReportLayout
  title="Desktop main composition · Agent Atelier"
      description="Maka Electron main: stores → tool assembly → BackendRegistry → SessionManager → IPC cluster — companion report, not a seventh worldview chapter. UI chrome: /guides/desktop-ui."
  nav={nav}
  activeHref={selfHref}
  locale={locale}
>
  <article class="report">
    <header class="masthead">
      <p class="masthead__eyebrow">Companion guide · Specimen: maka-agent · {t.doneLabel}</p>
      <h1>
        <span class="masthead__title-zh">Desktop main 组合</span>
        <span class="masthead__title-en">Desktop host composition</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="masthead__sub">
        How the product shell welds <code>@maka/runtime</code>’s SessionManager into Electron main: store
        plane, tool assembly, backend factory, IPC registration. Orthogonal to §01–§06 — enter via
        <a href={ch01}>§01 spine</a> / <a href={`${ch01}#sandbox`}>#sandbox</a>, then read this page.
      </p>
      <div class="masthead__meta">
        <span>Home · /guides/desktop-host</span>
        <span>Research · #72 · Task · #73</span>
        <span>
          <a href={localePath("zh", "guides/desktop-host")}>中文</a>
        </span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <Section
      id="scene"
      label="Desktop · Scene"
      title="Why the composition root is main, not the renderer"
      lede="Single-writer process + OS trust boundary: the renderer only invokes; it does not own Runtime."
    >
      <p>
        Desktop main is the product composition root: open persistence, assemble tools, register
        backends, construct <code>SessionManager</code>, then expose typed IPC through preload. When
        authorities conflict, <strong>code + contract tests win</strong>. This page does not teach CSS,
        Storybook, or e2e-fixture scenario catalogs — supervision chrome lives at
        <a href={localePath(locale, "guides/desktop-ui")}>/guides/desktop-ui</a>.
      </p>
      <blockquote class="pull">
        Renderer never constructs SessionManager; secrets never cross main→renderer.
      </blockquote>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="layers"
      label="Desktop · Layers"
      title="Five composition contracts"
      lede="Order is load-bearing: tools and backends must exist before SessionManager; services like onboarding bind after runtime."
    >
      <DiagramFigure
        caption="Fig. · stores → assembleDesktopTools → BackendRegistry → SessionManager → registerIpc cluster; footer pins the preload trust boundary."
        alt="Five-step horizontal flow: stores, tools, backends, SessionManager, with IPC cluster and trust bar below."
      >
        <DesktopMainCompositionFlow />
      </DiagramFigure>

      <ol class="plain-list numbered">
        <li>
          <strong>Stores</strong> — <code>@maka/storage</code> factories: session / agent-run / runtime
          events / shell-run / artifact / settings / MCP config / telemetry…
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Tools</strong> — <code>assembleDesktopTools</code>: sandbox manager, darwin filesystem
          worker, deferred tool economy, CU / browser / skill binding.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Backends</strong> —
          <code>BackendRegistry.register('ai-sdk', createAiSdkBackendFactory(…))</code>; E2E may
          last-write-wins override to <code>FakeBackend</code>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Runtime</strong> —
          <code>new SessionManager(&#123; store, runStore, backends, shellRuns, … &#125;)</code>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>IPC</strong> — <code>registerIpc()</code> cluster (sessions / entry / permissions /
          settings / mcp / app…), not one mega-handler.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="session-manager"
      label="Desktop · SessionManager"
      title="SessionManager constructor shape"
      lede="Product façade: sendMessage / stop / recover / listSessions; the tool loop lives inside the backend."
    >
      <div class="table-wrap" role="region" aria-label="SessionManager dependencies" tabindex="0">
        <table class="proto-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Dep</th>
              <th scope="col">Role</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>store</code> / <code>runStore</code> / <code>runtimeEventStore</code></td>
              <td>Session JSONL, AgentRun, event durability</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>shellRuns</code></td>
              <td>Managed Bash / PTY; pushes <code>shell-runs:update</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>backends</code></td>
              <td>ai-sdk / fake factory registry</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>childTools</code></td>
              <td>Child-agent tool surface (file-leaning subset)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>continuation inspectors</td>
              <td>Local safety probe + background-ops detection</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>artifact / compact hooks</td>
              <td>List artifacts per turn; history-compact cleanup</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>
        When the MCP tool snapshot changes, <code>runtime.refreshIdleBackends()</code> — main owns the
        manager; secrets stay off the renderer wire.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="tool-assembly"
      label="Desktop · Tools"
      title="assembleDesktopTools: sandbox and worker entry"
      lede="The tool surface is welded before SessionManager; economy defers schemas via load_tools."
    >
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>
          <code>createBuiltinSandboxManager</code> + optional <code>FilesystemWorkerClient</code> (darwin
          only) — detail in
          <a href={`${ch02}#filesystem-worker`}>§02 · #filesystem-worker</a> /
          <a href={`${ch02}#shell-side-effects`}>#shell-side-effects</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          Deferred groups (Rive / Office / browser / CU / orchestration) stay off the per-turn wire by
          default; <code>MAKA_DISABLE_DEFERRED_TOOLS</code> restores full advertisement.
        </li>
        <li>
          <code>assertProductBindingCatalogClean('desktop', …)</code> +
          <code>buildHostCapabilitiesFromBinding</code> pin the product binding catalog.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="ipc"
      label="Desktop · IPC"
      title="registerIpc cluster (honest inventory)"
      lede="Registrars split by domain; push channels never carry plaintext secrets."
    >
      <div class="table-wrap" role="region" aria-label="IPC registrar cluster" tabindex="0">
        <table class="proto-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Registrar</th>
              <th scope="col">Owns</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>registerSessionsIpc</code></td>
              <td>Session CRUD / send / stream / artifacts / CU overlay hooks</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>registerSessionEntryIpc</code></td>
              <td>Entry / quick-chat / onboarding-gated create</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>registerPermissionsIpc</code></td>
              <td>Permission mode / bot / CU capability input</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>registerSettingsIpc</code></td>
              <td>Settings patch + runtime effects</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>registerMcpIpcMain</code></td>
              <td>MCP config + idle backend refresh</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>app / project-root / gateway / …</td>
              <td>Window, project root, subscription &amp; connection satellites</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="skills-governance"
      label="Desktop · Skills governance"
      title="bundled / managed / workspace: governance lives in main"
      lede="Runtime scans bodies; Desktop owns locks, provenance, and marketplace taxonomy — do not mash them into one “skills system”."
    >
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Three sources</strong> — <code>workspace</code> (per project) ·
          <code>bundled</code> (product templates + <code>maka-bundled</code> lock + contentSha256) ·
          <code>managed</code> (<code>~/.maka/skill-sources</code>).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Closed categories</strong> — <code>MANAGED_SKILL_CATEGORIES</code> seven buckets;
          unknown front-matter falls back to <code>效率工具</code> so market filters stay bounded.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Install failure reasons</strong> —
          <code>cancelled</code> / <code>invalid_skill</code> / <code>already_exists</code> /
          <code>blocked_path</code> / <code>write_failed</code>; paths must pass
          <code>isPathInside</code> / <code>isSafeSkillId</code>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Bundled lock trust</strong> — only when content hash matches current or migratable
          legacy templates; forging <code>sourceType: bundled</code> is not privilege.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Enabled gate</strong> — Desktop <code>setSkillEnabled</code> writes governance;
          Runtime catalog excludes disabled at scan (see §01 <code>#skills</code>).
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Cross-body behavior contracts:
        <a href={localePath(locale, "guides/skills-corpus")}>/guides/skills-corpus</a>. Specimens:
        <code>apps/desktop/src/main/skills.ts</code> · <code>managed-skill-sources.ts</code> ·
        <code>bundled-skill-catalog.generated.ts</code>.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="pr-five"
      label="Desktop · Release gate"
      title="PR five questions (elevated from archive delivery contract)"
      lede="The non-negotiable rules in archive/full-product-test-plan still teach what “done” means — not the monthly schedule itself."
    >
      <ol class="plain-list numbered">
        <li><strong>Contract</strong> — which data / IPC / RuntimeEvent / persistence surface changed?</li>
        <li><strong>User Flow</strong> — which exact path can the user complete after merge?</li>
        <li><strong>Tests</strong> — which unit / storage / IPC / fixture / smoke covers it?</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Security</strong> — which trust boundary, secret, path, sandbox, or redaction rule applies?
        </li>
        <li><strong>Not Included</strong> — which adjacent work is explicitly scoped to another issue?</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        Still-Current fail gates: configured default model but old sessions block send; secrets/absolute
        paths leak to stdout/UI/telemetry; renderer reads arbitrary absolute paths; Markdown escapes the
        Electron sandbox; new UI lacks empty/loading/error/focus; deterministic cases covered only by
        manual gates.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="boundaries"
      label="Desktop · Boundaries"
      title="Not runtime-host, not headless"
      lede="Three product composition paths — do not collapse them."
    >
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Desktop main</strong> — Electron product shell + preload IPC (this page).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong><code>packages/runtime-host</code></strong> — optional local unix-socket thin host (four
          ops); see §01 <code>#runtime-host</code> lean note.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Headless / Harbor</strong> — eval / CLI composition without Electron preload.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Bot / IM bridges:
        <a href={localePath(locale, "guides/bot-im")}>/guides/bot-im</a>. Computer-use suite:
        <a href={localePath(locale, "guides/computer-use")}>/guides/computer-use</a>. Supervision UI:
        <a href={localePath(locale, "guides/desktop-ui")}>/guides/desktop-ui</a>. Trust model:
        <a href={localePath(locale, "guides/security-privacy")}>/guides/security-privacy</a>.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="failure"
      label="Desktop · Failure"
      title="Failure stories"
      lede="Composition failures should fail closed into user-visible states — not a half-wired runtime."
    >
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>Second instance → single-instance lock refuses; no parallel writers on one workspace ledger</li>
        <li>Invalid workspace / project root on send → refuse the turn; never silently land in the wrong tree</li>
        <li>Runtime effects fail after settings patch → do not pretend BotRegistry / MCP reconciled</li>
        <li>Preload asks for cleartext secrets → protocol refuse (masked only)</li>
        <li>MCP config change during active turn → old backend finishes before snapshot swap (no force-kill)</li>
        <li>Teaching Desktop main as the <code>runtime-host</code> four-op surface → teaching error</li>
        <li>Forged bundled lock / skipped <code>blocked_path</code> → skills governance breach</li>
        <li>PR ships UI without Contract/Tests/Security five questions → delivery-contract theater</li>
      </ul>
    </Section>

    <aside class="history-aside">
      <p class="history-aside__tag">Evolution aside · mechanism</p>
      <p>
        Verification entry points: wiring contracts under
        <code>apps/desktop/src/main/__tests__</code> (session lifecycle / task-ledger / single-instance,
        …). Outline:
        <code>docs/research/desktop-main-composition-deep-outline.md</code> (#72 → Task #73).
      </p>
    </aside>
  </article>
</ReportLayout>
